---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const alternates = {
  es: "/es/cookies",
  ca: "/ca/cookies",
  en: "/en/cookies",
};
---

<BaseLayout
  description="Cookie Policy: learn which cookies we use (technical, analytical and advertising), their purpose, and how to manage them."
  locale="en"
  {alternates}
>
  <Header locale="en" currentPath="/en/cookies" {alternates} />

  <!-- =========================
       HERO COOKIES
       ========================= -->
  <section class="ck-hero" aria-label="Cookie Policy Header">
    <div class="ck-hero__bg" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="ck-hero__inner container">
      <img class="ck-hero__icon" src="/assets/mark-hero.svg" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
      <h1 class="ck-hero__title">Cookie Policy</h1>
      <span class="ck-hero__meta">Last updated: October 21, 2025</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =========================
       CONTENT
       ========================= -->
  <section class="ck-section container" aria-labelledby="ck-title">
    <article class="ck-content">
      <p class="ck-lead">
        At Centro Dental Sueco S.L. (“Clínica Dental Sueca”, “we”, “us” or “our”) we use cookies and similar
        technologies to provide you with a better browsing experience, analyze traffic and show you personalized
        advertising based on your interests. This policy explains what cookies are, what types we use, their purpose
        and how you can manage them.
      </p>

      <div class="ck-block">
        <h2 id="ck-title">1. What are cookies?</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help remember your preferences,
          improve functionality, or analyze how you interact with the page. Some are essential for the website to work
          properly, while others help enhance your user experience or personalize content and ads.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="ck-block">
        <h2>2. Types of cookies we use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Technical or necessary cookies:</strong> essential for the website to function correctly and for features
              such as form submission.</li>
          <li><strong>Preference or customization cookies:</strong> remember settings like language or time zone.</li>
          <li><strong>Analytical cookies:</strong> allow us to measure traffic and user behavior. We use
              <strong>Google Analytics</strong> and similar tools to understand website usage.</li>
          <li><strong>Advertising cookies:</strong> used to display relevant ads or measure the effectiveness of our
              marketing campaigns through <strong>Google Ads</strong> and <strong>Meta Pixel (Facebook Pixel)</strong>.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="ck-block">
        <h2>3. Providers and purposes</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> measures interactions and site performance. More info:
              <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/cookies" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google policy</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Google Ads:</strong> shows personalized ads and tracks conversions.
              Policy: <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Meta Pixel (Facebook Pixel):</strong> tracks ad performance and creates custom audiences.
              More info: <a href="https://www.facebook.com/policies/cookies" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meta policy</a>.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="ck-block">
        <h2>4. Consent</h2>
        <p>
          When you access our site, an informational banner will appear allowing you to accept or reject the use of
          non-essential cookies. You can configure your preferences at any time through the “Cookie Settings” link
          located in the footer.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="ck-block">
        <h2>5. How to modify or delete cookies</h2>
        <p>
          You can allow, block, or delete cookies from your browser settings. Here’s how to do it in the main browsers:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings &gt; Privacy and Security &gt; Cookies and other site data</li>
          <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Options &gt; Privacy &amp; Security &gt; Cookies and Site Data</li>
          <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences &gt; Privacy</li>
          <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings &gt; Privacy, Search, and Services</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="ck-block">
        <h2>6. International data transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Providers such as Google or Meta may process data outside the European Economic Area (EEA). In such cases,
          we ensure adequate protection mechanisms are in place according to GDPR (Standard Contractual Clauses or
          adequacy decisions).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="ck-block">
        <h2>7. Policy updates</h2>
        <p>
          We may modify this policy to adapt it to legal or technical changes. Updated versions will always be available
          on this page.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="ck-block">
        <h2>8. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this Cookie Policy, you can email us at
          <strong>hola@dentalsueca.es</strong> with the subject “Cookies”.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <Footer locale="en" />
</BaseLayout>
